subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis adult.
Medium-size species, body length 
3.6–4.5 mm
(n=5); general color dark brown (
Fig. 3
); pedicel and postpedicel yellowish brown; arista with 12–14 rays; head sparsely golden tomentose (
Fig. 3B, C, D
); mesonotum golden tomentose with two (sometimes four) greyish stripes; scutellum flattened with one pair of small apical tubercles bearing marginal setae, without lateral tubercles (
Fig. 3B, C
); wings hyaline without infuscate pattern (
Fig. 3E
); femora black; tibiae brown; tarsi reddish brown (
Fig. 3A
) (
Lizarralde de Grosso 1998
; 
Zatwarnicki & Hagenlund 2017
).
